he switch has been flipped and Hydra is now available to TiVo Bolt, Roamio, and Mini owners who want it. However, you probably want to 
\xc2\xa0before proceeding. Further, the downgrade app, should you later choose to throw in the towel, does not yet appear to be available and TiVo Minis\xc2\xa0
hould that not be enough to dissuade, here\xe2\x80\x99s how to get in early on the optional upgrade:\xc2\xa0
, log into TiVo.com, and select the boxes you\xe2\x80\x99d like to update. The TiVo Service Numbers are being swept in every two hours so, should the 24-48 hour wait be too long, you\xe2\x80\x99d go into your network settings to force a connection to receive the update and then reboot to apply it.
Keep in mind any Minis you have will ultimately need to match the host DVR interface. So excluding them or trying to prioritize them within the request form won\xe2\x80\x99t ultimately mean anything. With that in mind, I\xe2\x80\x99d suggest updating everything or nothing.
I haven\xe2\x80\x99t had enough time with Hydra to pass judgement, other than to say I appreciate 
\xc2\xa0and find the animations, transitions, etc very smooth \xe2\x80\xa6 although there\xe2\x80\x99s going to be significant retraining in regards to deprecation of the left directional button and rethinking of the now playing show info banner, plus who knows what else. Also, at a meta analytical level, the new interface has me wondering what makes TiVo a TiVo. Hm.
