I upgraded my Roamio OTA and two Gen1 Minis last night.  The Roamio and one Gen1 went as expected.  The second Mini gave an error stating that the upgrade failed and to try again.  It also said to check my internet connection.  The internet connection was fine, so I tried again and it again failed.  So, I pulled the plug, rebooted it and it immediately went into installing the update.  Once completed, it booted up and worked as expected.
I use Harmony remotes, so I had to map a button for the \xe2\x80\x98Back\xe2\x80\x99 button.  However, the Harmony database didn\xe2\x80\x99t list a \xe2\x80\x98Back\xe2\x80\x99 button but I found it is called \xe2\x80\x98Return\xe2\x80\x99 on their list.  I mapped it to the \xe2\x80\x98Previous\xe2\x80\x99 button and will have to train my fingers to use that instead of the \xe2\x80\x98Left\xe2\x80\x99 button to return to the previous screen.
