ave, with the \xe2\x80\x9cwhat makes TiVo a TiVo\xe2\x80\x9d comment, does the new interface feel more generic, even though it\xe2\x80\x99s supposedly making better use of the screen real estate?  Did they lose the TiVo sounds or other things that are key TiVo?  My concern with Hydra, beyond the big, ugly bar of programming icons (which I read can be disabled) is the possibility that it no longer feels like a TiVo.  I didn\xe2\x80\x99t feel that way with the Premiere when I got that with the updated interface (even though it was slooooow), but the look of Hydra has me both intrigued and frightened for not only the future of the software that I use, but the future of TiVo.   I\xe2\x80\x99m sure they will tweak it to improve, but it comes back to what makes it a TiVo?  As long as we have our One Pass, My Shows list with everything we are used to, and the Live Guide (oops, minus one), I will be better equipped to \xe2\x80\x9csurvive\xe2\x80\x9d such a change,
I am not sure why everyone is freaking out about Hydra.  Yes there are changes but this should be expected of new software.  I know that in the past TiVo would mostly innovate on features not UI, maybe that is why so many people are worried Hydra won\xe2\x80\x99t work for them.  I think Hydra is a big step forward, all the menus are in HD, there is a great use of realestate new icons are easy to read and make guide actually better if you ask me I am 100% happy with it and looking forward to new features.
I though what makes TiVo is OnePass, 8s rewind, 30s fast forward, commercial skip, etc. and all that is there in much nicer packaging suitable for 21st century not 1990\xe2\x80\x99s.
\xe2\x80\x9cDave, with the \xe2\x80\x9cwhat makes TiVo a TiVo\xe2\x80\x9d comment\xe2\x80\xa6\xe2\x80\x9d
I initially puzzled over that formulation too.
I\xe2\x80\x99ve come to believe it\xe2\x80\x99s an exceedingly polite way of saying the TiVo mascot has suddenly become a character in the film 
FYI If you have Minis in the mix, I wouldn\xe2\x80\x99t upgrade to Hydra at this point. Many of us are still losing connectivity throughout the day to host DVR with V66 error. Requires Mini reboot. My wife is not happy. Also couldn\xe2\x80\x99t figure out how to get to her recordings this AM and called me at work, but that will come with time.
I got my 4K Mini Vox hooked up
, but haven\xe2\x80\x99t tried voice yet. Didn\xe2\x80\x99t want to risk waking my sick daughter last night. Several apps are missing at this point, including Amazon. TiVo\xe2\x80\x99s going through the certification process with them, but keeps updating the software build which kinda resets thing. Hopefully they get that sorted in the next few weeks.
Jakub, certainly all of those features are key to making TiVo what it is, but I have all of those things in an HD interface that is easy to navigate, and fully functional.  All menus on the gen3 UI are updated now, and I\xe2\x80\x99m surprised to hear it referred to as \xe2\x80\x9c1990s\xe2\x80\x9d-esque.
I\xe2\x80\x99d like to see something that would make me want to move to Hydra beyond just a mixed-review (so far) UI change that loses the Live Guide (which I use a lot).  I know TiVo wants search to be the primary way you find programming, and I use that frequently, too, but sometimes I just scroll through the Live Guide and its hit-and-miss data to see what is out there, and cross my fingers that it\xe2\x80\x99s accurate.   
hat said, to each his/her own, and I don\xe2\x80\x99t begrudge TiVo for making this change, since the made it optional.   I will likely update at some point in the future when the issues are worked out, but hoping they bring back Live Guide before I do.  If so, I can get used to an inteface change, and may even grow to like it.
Just for reference if you upgrade now and decide you don\xe2\x80\x99t like it, there is currently no rollback method released publicly. It\xe2\x80\x99s coming but no idea when.
I find Hydra to be a far more streamlined and user-friendly interface. It\xe2\x80\x99s also, IMO, far prettier.
What makes a Tivo a Tivo ? A DVR that does OTA and Cable you can own, that can be easily be hooked directly to a TV, and doesn\xe2\x80\x99t force you into streaming devices to view recordings.
\n   When the smoke clears most of Tivo\xe2\x80\x99s OTA only competition won\xe2\x80\x99t be around. I actually use OTA but acknowledge cable isn\xe2\x80\x99t going away. Rovi knows this too.
\xe2\x80\x9cWhat makes a Tivo a Tivo ? A DVR that does OTA and Cable you can own, that can be easily be hooked directly to a TV, and doesn\xe2\x80\x99t force you into streaming devices to view recordings.\xe2\x80\x9d
Well, I\xe2\x80\x99ve been a TiVo devotee for about a decade, and that\xe2\x80\x99s never how I\xe2\x80\x99ve seen the \xe2\x80\x9cWhat makes a TiVo a TiVo\xe2\x80\x9d question.
For one, I got into TiVo before streaming was a thing. I love OnePass, but I\xe2\x80\x99d still be a TiVo user if it had never come about.
For two, while I appreciate the \xe2\x80\x9cI own it\xe2\x80\x9d part, that\xe2\x80\x99s only because I live in a metro area with 3 competing MSO\xe2\x80\x99s, and I\xe2\x80\x99ve been able to easily bargain them down in price using my TiVo as leverage. (And that\xe2\x80\x99s partially because I\xe2\x80\x99ve been genuinely 
But really, for me at least, what \xe2\x80\x9cWhat makes a TiVo a TiVo\xe2\x80\x9d is 
I came late to the party. For years, I had a wonderful CableCo Scientific Atlanta DVR that I loved. It had a UX that was quite similar to the pre-Encore TiVo, minus the superior remote. I read about TiVo, and while it seemed like it had a slightly better UX than the SA box, it didn\xe2\x80\x99t seem significant to me.
hen my CableCo contacted me and told me they were going to force us to switch out the Scientific Atlanta box for one from a different manufacturer. I got the model number, did a day of internet research on this box\xe2\x80\x99s UX, and I was 
. Within a few days, I had done enough research to greenlight a TiVo, and that was that.
(As it turned out, the TiVo UX was significantly better than the Scientific Atlanta UX in many subtle ways that I wasn\xe2\x80\x99t aware of.)
But for a decade, that\xe2\x80\x99s \xe2\x80\x9cwhat makes a TiVo a TiVo\xe2\x80\x9d has meant to me simply: 
Windows wasn\xe2\x80\x99t a TiVo. Dunno about Moxi, but I\xe2\x80\x99ve got doubts.
nd frankly, pretty much 90% of what I\xe2\x80\x99m hearing about Hydra is telling me it may well not be \xe2\x80\x9ca TiVo\xe2\x80\x9d. I suspect I\xe2\x80\x99ll try Hydra out at some point, but even little stuff like making Peanut use less mental-friction-free is what gives me Halloween frights.
nd if Hydra is as screwed up for non-voice usage as I\xe2\x80\x99m currently perceiving, then MJR\xe2\x80\x99s note about integrated streaming will 
