I have parental controls set. After the Hydra upgrade, none of my saved recordings would play. They all come up with an error indicating that they can\xe2\x80\x99t be played, and refer me to error P103 (tivo.com/help/p103). If you look at the details it shows this error relates to Parental Controls.
Yes, that\xe2\x80\x99s right \xe2\x80\x93 all my previous recordings won\xe2\x80\x99t play because they are protected by parental controls \xe2\x80\x93 and the system doesn\xe2\x80\x99t prompt for the parental controls pin. The easy workaround is to either disable parental controls, or just unlock it for 4 hours with the menu.
I, too discovered the Parental Controls issue but none of my shows would play \xe2\x80\x93 even the ones that passed the Parental Controls restriction.  Someone in the forums suggested disabling PC and it worked, but it\xe2\x80\x99s a totally unacceptable glitch.  This is a system that is designed to know the patterns of those watching \xe2\x80\x93 for instance, kid shows are supposed to be displayed during kid hours, but it\xe2\x80\x99s not smart enough to operate with parental controls enabled.  How this was not discovered before rollout is beyond me.
