iVo Nearing Wider Deployment of \xe2\x80\x98Project Hydra\xe2\x80\x99 UI
eeking consumers to try out its new interface
6/09/2017
If a move toward field trials offers any indication, TiVo appears to be inching toward the wider rollout of a new user interface code-named \xe2\x80\x9cProject Hydra.\xe2\x80\x9d
Margaret Schmidt, TiVo\xe2\x80\x99s chief design officer and vice president of product development, recently tweeted that the company was seeking people to try it out, directing them to a 
 TiVo official confirmed that this is for a beta trial of the Project Hydra user interface. Vodafone Espa\xc3\xb1a was the 
iVo has not announced a date for the wider launch and expanded availability of the new UI, but the beta test site notes that TiVo is targeting a new software release for \xe2\x80\x9clate 2017.\xe2\x80\x9d
Gadget blogger Dave Zatz points out that the release timing is far behind the original schedule:\xc2\xa0
Late 2017 only puts it one year behind schedule. ;) 
iVo presented some details on its redesigned and streamlined interface in February, noting that operators will have the ability to customize it with their branding and through the use of different colors. It will offer a more unified look and feel across different devices.
lso included is something Schmidt refers to as a \xe2\x80\x9ctrade-up experience\xe2\x80\x9d in which the viewer can use the arrow keys to drill down into content. Clicking right shows what programming the other tuners on the box is pulling in, left pulls up the user\xe2\x80\x99s favorite channels, down presents the prediction strip, and up offers a presentation of what\xe2\x80\x99s on different channels, including what\xe2\x80\x99s on now and what\xe2\x80\x99s coming next.
he new UI also borrows a page from TV\xe2\x80\x99s past with support for a standard grid guide, an option that Sling TV recently added to its interface.
