"I'm thinking you have the updated version, how do you like it?"
\n\n\n\n\t\t\t\t\tOverall I like it a lot. Much more graphical in nature than the previous version.  As usual when making a sea change in the look and feel, it is taking a bit of time to get used to the differences.  A few things are missing but a Tivo rep has said they are working on it and updates should be coming along fairly soon.
\n1.  Lost the live guide, only a grid guide is there.  Live guide is very handy when you\xe2\x80\x99re looking for something on a particular channel, like a new show, and aren\xe2\x80\x99t sure when it is coming.
\n2. Channel sorting is only by channel number, no option to sort by channel name.
\nUpgrading to the software went smoothly on the Bolt and Roamio, but the minis fought it a bit.  Usually just a power pull restart would get things going on the gen 2 Minis.  Gen 1 minis fought harder from what I read, not sure that got fixed yet.
\nWith the new Vox hardware is a new remote that incorporates voice, the new remote is available separately and I\xe2\x80\x99ve got mine ordered.
