his comment has been rated as unhelpful by Slickdeals users
11-22-2017
\n 1) will the Mini also be able to see the Bolt?
\r\nYes. You can pick which DVR to join and you can switch. The available DVRs (any TiVo on the same network) will show at the bottom of the recording list. 
"\r\n2) Will the Roamio Pro and the Bolt be able to see each other's recordings?"
"\r\nYes, but not all in one menu. You can see the recordings from the box you are controlling by pressing the TiVo button. At the bottom of the menu are the other available TiVos. If you select one, it will take you to that box's recordings list. "
"\r\n3) if the mini can't see the bolt, can you transfer recordings between the bolt and Roamio Pro?"
\r\nNot applicable as they can see each other. Menus function the same. You can delete recordings, etc.  there is no way to transfer between TiVos- at least that I am aware. 
\r\nI have a TiVo Bolt, Roamio, and Mini on my network. They just work.\n 
\nThanks for the update.  I looking forward to getting it hooked up.\n        
his comment has been rated as unhelpful by Slickdeals users
11-22-2017
\n Which 4TB WD drive did you buy?\n 
\nThere is a very reputable seller on fleabay named "central_valley_computer_parts_inc" (with underscores) that sells good WD drives that you cannot buy in stores.  I bought a "70 Hours" drive from him for $163 shipped.  I know hard drives well and tested it thoroughly with my linux server (put 48 hours on it testing).  The drive also only had 55 hours on it when I got it.  They sell drives that have zero hours, 50 hours, 70 hours, 300 hours... just pick your price point and buy one.  They were having a sale when I bought the 70 hour drive and it was the cheapest of all their 4TB drives at a time.  They also have 3TB and 5TB drives.
"\nBe aware that with the BOLT if you go larger than 3TB you can't just put it directly into the BOLT.  You have to prep the drive in a Windows PC first, but it is very easy.  All the info is on tivocommunity forum."
\nAfter I posted on tivocommunity about buying the drive several others also posted back that they had also bought drives from the same seller with perfect results.  They have a 30 day money back guaranty also.
