iVo Hydra - Not a fan so far
"I upgraded my 1TB Tivo Roamio OTA and Tivo Mini to Hydra a few weeks ago hoping the new interface would make them feel more modern.  While it does feel more modern to some extent, I don't think it's worth all the quirks, bugs, and poor design decisions."
"I've been keeping track of my complaints, none of which were an issue on the previous version.  Here is what I have so far, which I "
he back button being required instead of being able to use the left button is annoying.  Suggestion: allow both the back button and left button to have the same function when appropriate.
he guide up/down buttons changing the entire page instead of going to the next channel is annoying.  That\xe2\x80\x99s what the channel up/down button is for.  Why was this changed?
he My Shows gigantic bar with pictures takes up too much space.  Add an option to turn it off.
he smaller text is harder to see in the Guide, My Shows, etc.
he guide shows the wrong listing for a single channel of mine. Guide lists the programming of the channel I cannot get, yet viewing channel shows content of the channel in my area.
My Shows are sorted by episode instead of recorded date by default. I prefer sorting by recorded date and have to change it every time.  Please allow changing the default sorting method.
My Tivo Roamio intermittently stops outputting sound on antenna.  This was not a problem on the previous version.  Restarting or switching to an app and then back resolves.
My Tivo Mini intermittently loses connection to Roamio. Restarting Mini resolves.
everting to the previous version requires wiping all content and schedules.  This is not a good user experience.  The operating system should be stored separately from the content.
o you guys agree or disagree?  Am I being too picky?  What do you guys think of Hydra?
Wholeheartedly agree. It\xe2\x80\x99s like someone at TiVo who had never before used a TiVo\xe2\x80\x94and had only had the experience described to them in vague terms\xe2\x80\x94was tasked with designing the Hydra UI. It just doesn\xe2\x80\x99t feel \xe2\x80\x9cTiVo\xe2\x80\x9d to me. Things are unnecessarily complicated, and some of the changes feel completely arbitrary. For example, it seems like the threshold for prompting the deletion of a show once you\xe2\x80\x99re towards the end has been changed. Whereas before I could head back to the menu right as the credits started to roll and get that prompt, now it seems hit or miss. I also hate the new \xe2\x80\x9cFavorite Channels\xe2\x80\x9d stuff that\xe2\x80\x99s been assigned to the left arrow button on the remote. It\xe2\x80\x99s counterintuitive and users should at least have the option of restoring the legacy functionality.
his is the stuff devs should be interested in hearing.
1000TimesThis
here are some good ideas and feature in it but some basic things (like what you mentioned plus a few more) are really disappointing. TiVo has been known for their amazing user experience and seems like it went out the door too fast. I\xe2\x80\x99m hoping they change it because as is this could be the start of the end for TiVo and that would be such a shame. I hope they realize how serious this is. If the interface isn\xe2\x80\x99t amazing then just use the cable providers box and save money. 
"Yep, it's the interface and multiple integrations that brought me to TiVo. If it goes to shit I'll probably just switch to using my TV since it has native support for the popular streaming apps along with OTA antenna. I'd just be missing the DVR functionality, which can be supplimented."
I upgraded a spare Roamio and will not be touching my Bolt or Roamio Pro. 
You\xe2\x80\x99ve provided a great write up and I can\xe2\x80\x99t help but feel like a beta tester. This is clearly a whole new system not an upgrade, otherwise some core things like left to go back or live guide would still be applicable. 
Without an easy way to downgrade, I\xe2\x80\x99m going to hold tight until some of the kinks are smoothed out. This feels like the whole guide data fiasco. 
common tasks should be quick and fluid.  They are not.  3 clicks to play or delete after the horrid navigation through a crappy sliding UI is ridiculous.
the UI should be consistent and predictable.  It is not.  It is all over the friggin place.  Get huge thumbnails moving down through recordings, but after moving back to the top it is now text only again.
the UI should be configurable.  Why can\'t the "show all" grid be my preferred default behavior?  Why must I use the sliding bullshit that looks like something better suited for a phone swipe interface (but it would suck ass there too.)
there is no clear indication of where you are or what you are doing in the UI at any time.  What an incoherent mess!
"I'd much prefer actual ingenuity over what looks like a script kiddie high school webui project.  Oooh!  Lookit our graphics and effects!  That animation is rad!"
"Instead of worthless side menu for tuners, how about  a full screen grid of what's on all tuners, and a way to highlight each to change their channels?   How about some flexible pip stuff in general?  I have four friggin tuners.  Let me interact with them to my advantage "
"Instead we get the worthless side menus that don't convey things nearly as well as a simple select on live TV used to."
verything about this is half-baked and a far worse "experience".  I don\'t want an experience.  I want a clean ui that gets it done and gets out of the way.  I\'m not here to play with your ui.  I\'m here to navigate my media.  TiVo has forgotten that with this garbage.
"I agree about the back button (#1). That is incredibly frustrating. Of the rest of the things, I don't think it's an issue for me. Honestly never noticed/don't have that issue for #2-#5. #6 sounds like an annoying bug. I do agree that if you have a preferred sort method (#7) then you should be able to retain that preferred method. #8-#9 also sound like bugs, as I'm sure you had no issue before with connectivity or sound. #10 just flat out sucks - first off I didn't know there would be a way to revert, but doing so wipes out content? Stupid."
he biggest complaint from my house is that they took away the "PLAY ALL" feature for folders. This stops us from being able to marathon shows, forcing us to interact with the device at the end of every episode. Not too much of an issue for me or my wife when we are watching our shows, but a huge hassle for our small kids who just want to watch 10 episodes of Paw Patrol uninterrupted on a rainy weekend.
hydra is junk to me. i rolled back my units and planning my exit strategy because i cant imagine this getting better. maybe a bug fix here and there but this is the direction. no thanks. 
o glad this is not forced upgrade.  I hope it never is.  The current UI is perfect.  
"Tivo, please don't force us to update.  (I have a Roamio OTA)"
. The show preview panes are nicer, the show listings are cleaner with respect to seasons.
he one feature that Hydra grabbed me with was the 
. We always struggled to see what was playing on the TV behind that thing in the past, now I can see right through it. Seriously, it is just stunning that it took that long to get transparent controls.
My wife loves the new favorite channels interface. I like the customization of apps you can do in the menus, we use Plex and Netflix quite a bit, this way of opening those apps is much cleaner than before. I also like that it seems to be watching me to determine 
I miss being able to hit TiVo-2 for to-do list, TiVo-4 for search. Those mnemonics just made 
. If I can customize TiVo-5 thru 9, why change the established numbers for 0-4 and make them inflexible?
We\'re hitting the "minis can\'t connect" garbage, not as frequently as previously, they say that\'s "fixed", who knows where that is in the rollout tho.
My main wish for this new interface is that they\'ll explore skinning. Customizing the colors and views should be easy given the modularity they seem to be building into things. I also hope they revisit some of the design choices. Looking at "My Shows" feels odd, the scrolling is weird and most of the screen is blank even with the preview panes of episodes.
"I'm looking forward to bugfixes and feature enhancements."
For your #9, a soft/network restart is faster than restarting the mini.
