FYI - A report that TiVo appears to be preparing a new set-top box called "Mavrik" that would stream video content over the Internet, possibly even combining local channels and streaming services in tier packages
iVo Mavrik is an OTA Cloud DVR!
By Dave Zatz, Zatz Not Funny! - November 8, 2016
iVO Cooking up OTA Cloud Recording & Streaming DVR [32] comments
FYI - More info on the TiVo Mavrik box
By Dave Zatz, Zatz Not Funny! - March 6, 2017
iVo Mavrik\xe2\x80\x99s FCC confidentiality has lifted\xe2\x80\xa6 suggesting the unannounced cord cutting solution is behind schedule but treating us to even more pre-release photos and intel on the product (\xc2\xbb
). It\xe2\x80\x99s pretty clear at this point that Mavrik is a Tablo-esque network tuner that streams live over-the-air television and DVR recordings to set-tops, like Fire TV, and mobile devices. While we know Mavrik will offer a cloud DVR service, a la Boxee, it\xe2\x80\x99s not clear if the two-tuner, headless set-top will also record locally via included SD slot or USB-attached storage.
More FCC analysis from the TiVo Community indicate the Mavrik incorporates Bolt-level processing and transcoding capabilities, an 8GB cache, and 512MB of memory. Beyond Tablo, also active in this space is Channels which utilizes HDHomeRun hardware to pipe live (or recorded) television into Apple TV and iPhone or iPad. 
