eviewer Rating 1 out of 5 stars 
"The bolt+ has a major issue with its HDMI. It won't always display signal sent from the tv. In order to get it working you need to unpliug and plug in again the HDMI cable pretty much every time you sit down to watch live tv or a recorded show. I even replaced the HDMI cable but it didn't solver anything. Customer Support at TiVo won't acknowledge the problem and just asks you to reboot the box. Once rebooted it works once and then they hang up on you claiming you are fixed.\r\nI did a little research and saw others had the same issue.\r\nIt may work fine with your television. Personally, its too much money for me to roll the dice had I known."
o, I would not\xc2\xa0recommend this to a friend
eviewer Rating 5 out of 5 stars 
"This is an amazing DVR. Other TIVO DVR's are excellent, but this one is incredible. Six tuners, 3 terabytes of hard disk space, amazing abilities to fast forward with reasonable voice, or even faster (about 3X) with captions, other fast forward options significantly better than DVR's from Comcast or Dish which I have used. It is able to skip commercials with a single press of a button. Its search function which covers all the streaming services plus Comcast is second to none. I no longer need a bunch of remotes controls (e.g. ROKU, Amazon, etc.) and the device is already 4K ready. And the tech support is great! Totally recommended."
eviewer Rating 4 out of 5 stars 
I love this machine and I gave it 4 stars only because like the traditional cable box it doesn\'t display the time of day and it doesn\'t have the RF TV Out. The RF TV Out is important to me because I have a DVD recorder and I haven\'t figured out how to record tv programs to the recorder.\r\nI bought this box because despite the fact that I selected "Keep Until I Delete" Verizon Fios took it upon itself to delete programs when I ran out of space.
eviewer Rating 5 out of 5 stars 
"We love this DVR! I've had several TiVo boxes over the years and this is by far the best . Skip mode is awesome, tons of storage and the remote is very responsive. Spend the extra money on the 3TB of storage, you won't regret it"
eviewer Rating 5 out of 5 stars 
"The TiVo unit was a great buy along with the TiVo minis. We couldn't be happier with the set up."
eviewer Rating 3 out of 5 stars 
"Even though this is the high end Tivo Bolt with 6 tuners, it doesn't seem to properly utilize all 6 at once. Even with no apparent programming overlap it keeps showing conflicts and won't record on all 6 tuners at the same time. Also, the error messages for recording conflicts are very confusing and of no help in figuring out how to resolve.\r\nAlso, level of personal customization is sadly lacking, and in some cases just doesn't work, like channel list removal of stations you have no interest in. I uncheck them in the list which is supposed to make them not show up, but they still do.\r\nGeneral performance is slow also. I get a lot of pauses and spinning wheels when there should be no issues, such as not while using on-demand, etc."
o, I would not\xc2\xa0recommend this to a friend
eviewer Rating 2 out of 5 stars 
Hands down the best DVR on the planet. Onepass and the Tivo iOS app are terrific, Guide is awesome, Skipmode is the best thing since sliced bread. Why only a two star rating? Because this box fails as a 4K streaming device. The Bolt differentiates itself from previous versions with the ability to stream 4K content. It works for Netflix and Youtube but not much else. I was hoping to watch Amazon Prime 4K content but I can\'t. Vudu has a bunch of 4K UHD titles that I cannot watch using this 4K "Unified Entertainment System". That is pure marketing BS by Tivo and a major disappointment on a product with an ultra premium price tag. I thought I could get rid of my Roku for 4K content but boy was I wrong. Guidance from Tivo regarding future HDR capabilities would be helpful but customer service reps don\'t know what HDR is.
eviewer Rating 5 out of 5 stars 
"The unit performed admirably once I got it up and running. The problem connecting it with the cable company wasn't with the DVR but the cable company's inability to properly pair the Motorola cable modem card that they provided. But after 3 days of going back and forth I finally got to a desk jockey at the local Vyve connection desk that was willing to go the extra mile and find the correct procedure for this relatively new model. Has performed flawlessly ever since. If you want to own your own DVR on your cable TV network then this is the one to get. 6 tuners means hardly ever a conflict of time with your favorite programs. And 3Tb of space provides ample room to save lots of programs. And if that isn't enough you can get an optional external drive. We've recorded many shows in the 26 days since it was connected and are only at 15% of the useable space on the hard drive."
eviewer Rating 5 out of 5 stars 
"I don't need 50 characters to explain. It does what they advertise and works perfectly"
eviewer Rating 5 out of 5 stars 
